  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink295-kilavi">talaimakaṉ varaiviṭai vaittup pirintu nīṭṭittuḻi yuṭaṉ ceṉṟa neñciṉait talaimakaḷ niṉaintu kūṟiyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> 
          What the heroine, thinking of the heart that had gone along with him, said, when the hero, having fixed the time for marriage, parted and prolonged (his absence).              
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink295">
<l>varuvatu kollō tāṉē vārā</l>
<l>tavaṇuṟai mēvali ṉamaivatu kollō</l>
<l>puṉavar koḷḷiyiṟ pukalvaru maññai</l>
<l>yiruvi yirunta kuruvi varuntuṟap</l>
<l>pantāṭu makaḷiriṟ paṭartaruṅ</l>
<l>kuṉṟukeḻu nāṭaṉoṭu ceṉṟaveṉ ṉeñcē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>My heart, which went to the man of the hill-country,</l>
        <l>where the peacock, coming [back] to [its] residence</l>
        <l>because of the firebrands of the highland dwellers,</l>
        <l>sets out like women playing ball,</l>
        <l>while sparrows seated on the stubble suffer—</l>
        <l rend="space">will it come back?</l>
        <l>or, not coming, will it remain [there],</l>
        <l>out of desire for dwelling there?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
